  "question_id": "9a4655f3-d342-4429-8b11-730284fe17c4",
  "short_text": "Right Angled Triangle - 6",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print the **Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\n\n```\n      *\n    * *\n  * * *\n* * * *\n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as the **Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 6`,\n\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **6** rows as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-right-angled-triangle-6.png' widthPercent='60'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates the two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Star in box indicates the star and a space (\"* \").\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n          *\n        * *\n      * * *\n    * * * *\n  * * * * *\n* * * * * *\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "52bea931-8588-4d76-98d0-ba699e20c9a8",
      "code_content": "rows = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, rows + 1):\n    \n    spaces = \"  \" * (rows - each_number)\n    stars = \"* \" * (each_number)\n    print(spaces + stars)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
